        {
          "type": "frame",
          "id": "6ZB77",
          "name": "正文内容区",
          "width": "fill_container",
          "fill": "#0a0a0a",
          "gap": 48,
          "padding": [
            64,
            220
          ],
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "TWEzB",
              "name": "正文主栏",
              "width": 760,
              "layout": "vertical",
              "gap": 26,
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "GcV4b",
                  "name": "text1",
                  "fill": "#E7E0D2",
                  "content": "Most digital essays die in daylight. They are easy to read,\nquick to scan, and quickly forgotten. A gothic reading\nexperience does the opposite: it slows the eye, sharpens\nattention, and gives words enough shadow to breathe.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.35,
                  "fontFamily": "Cormorant Garamond",
                  "fontSize": 24,
                  "fontWeight": "normal",
                  "fontStyle": "italic"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "ja0xU",
                  "name": "text2",
                  "fill": "#E7E0D2",
                  "content": "When heading forms feel carved instead of typed, readers\nbegin to treat the text as place, not feed. The page becomes\na room. Contrast becomes architecture. Margins become silence.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.35,
                  "fontFamily": "Cormorant Garamond",
                  "fontSize": 24,
                  "fontWeight": "normal",
                  "fontStyle": "italic"
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "iDrIS",
                  "name": "quote",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "fill": "#111111",
                  "padding": [
                    24,
                    28
                  ],
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "Jo1cw",
                      "name": "quoteText",
                      "fill": "#EEDDB5",
                      "content": "\"Good typography does not\ndecorate thought. It conducts it.\"",
                      "lineHeight": 1.15,
                      "fontFamily": "Cinzel",
                      "fontSize": 26,
                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "OTYul",
                  "name": "text3",
                  "fill": "#E7E0D2",
                  "content": "I design each article as a sequence of emotional temperatures:\ninvitation, weight, clarity, and release. This is functional drama\nfor people who still read to think.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.35,
                  "fontFamily": "Cormorant Garamond",
                  "fontSize": 24,
                  "fontWeight": "normal",
                  "fontStyle": "italic"
                }
              ]
            },
